article.headline: Missouri St. 101, Cent. Arkansas 61
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Kyle Weems scored a season-high 20 points to lead six Missouri State players in double digits as part of a 101-61 thumping of Central Arkansas on Saturday night. Adam Leonard helped out with 16 points, including four 3-pointers, for Missouri State (6-2). Nafis Ricks and Nathan Scheer each added 13 while Will Creekmore and Caleb Patterson each chipped in with 12. Missouri State shot 61.3 percent from the floor and led by as many as 45 points late in the game. Imad Qahwash led Central Arkansas with 12 points while Dewan Clayborn, Chris Henson and Mark Rutledge each added 10. Central Arkansas shot just 39.6 percent from the floor.
